
The EWS Final PRC meeting will be held on July 10 at the St. Regis Hotel, 
Colonnade Room from 8:00 am until 4:00 pm.  Following the PRC meeting, we 
will have a social hour in the room adjacent to the Colonnade Room, from 
4:00-6:00pm.

The purpose of the meeting is to review each of the following EWS business 
units' distribution curves,  review promotion nominations to Director and Sr. 
Director, and  finalize the preranking of Vice Presidents in preparation for 
the final Enron-wide PRC meeting on July 23.  Representatives from the 
Enron-wide PRC Committee will attend this part of the meeting as observers.

The business units included in the meeting are:

Enron Americas
Enron Global Markets
Enron Industrial Markets
Enron Networks
Enron Global Assets and Services
Enron Engineering and Operational Services

Attached is a complete agenda for the meeting.  

